Ad Text:
Our purpose

Here at Datacom we connect people and technology in order to solve challenges, create opportunities and discover new possibilities for the communities we live in

About the Role (your why)

The way we work and our customer needs are changing! We are going through a significant AI uplift that will be a real game changer in the ANZ Market. Our customers are loving our story and excited about our new service solutions. As such we are seeking a Senior/Tech lead developers who want to get on board our journey. We need someone who is passionate about AI development and wants to push boundaries. Your software background is key but your passion for AI is a must. This role will see you will join our Digital Engineering team, focusing on delivering innovative AI-driven software solutions. We will offer you opportunity to work on cutting-edge projects, collaborating with cross-functional teams to design, develop, and use the latest AI Models that address complex business challenges. We need multiple people but we need them now so please don't hesitate this is your chance to put an ANZ company on the global map!!!

What you’ll bring

Must-haves

7+ years professional software development (Python and Typescript preferred) with production ML/AI experience
Demonstrated delivery of at least one generative-AI solution in production (chatbot, summariser, code assistant, etc.)
Deep familiarity with transformers and orchestration stacks such as LangChain v0.2+, LlamaIndex or Semantic Kernel
Practical experience deploying or fine-tuning models on Azure OpenAI / AI Foundry or AWS Bedrock / SageMaker
Hands-on with RAG patterns, vector databases and evaluation metrics (BLEU, ROUGE-L, GPTScore)
Cloud-native engineering skills: Docker, Kubernetes (AKS/EKS), infra-as-code and automated testing

Nice-to-haves

Agent frameworks (AutoGen 0.2/0.4, CrewAI) and tool-using agents. 
Multimodal model workflows (image-text with GPT-4o, Gpt4o real time API).
Experience with embedding models
Workspace automation using agentic frameworks
Advanced RAG variants – familiarity with LongRAG, Self-RAG, GraphRAG and the trade-offs between leading vector stores (Pinecone, Qdrant, FAISS, Azure AI Search)
Multimodal & streaming LLMs – delivering real-time GPT-4o or Gemini 2 Ultra use-cases (image to text or speech) and cross-modal embeddings.

Why join us here at Datacom?

Datacom is one of Australia and New Zealand’s largest suppliers of Information Technology professional services. We have managed to maintain a dynamic, agile, small business feel that is often diluted in larger organisations of our size. It's our people that give Datacom its unique culture and energy that you can feel from the moment you meet with us.

We care about our people and provide a range of perks such as social events, chill-out spaces, remote working, flexi-hours and professional development courses to name a few. You’ll have the opportunity to learn, develop your career, connect and bring your true self to work. You will be recognised and valued for your contributions and be able to do your work in a collegial, flat-structured environment.

We operate at the forefront of technology to help Australia and New Zealand’s largest enterprise organisations explore possibilities and solve their greatest challenges, so you will never run out of interesting new challenges and opportunities.

We want Datacom to be an inclusive and welcoming workplace for everyone and take pride in the steps we have taken and continue to take to make our environment fun and friendly, and our people feel supported.

Who are we?

Australian owned, Brown & Watson International (BWI) have led the way with an enviable portfolio of innovative and market-leading brands that hold their own on a world stage within the automotive industry.  Specialising in automotive electrical and lighting products, as well as portable power management and vehicle accessories, we have a stable of established industry names including NARVA, Projecta, Philips Automotive, OSRAM, Vision X, Big Red Gear, KT Cable, BOAB, Maxi-Lite, Twisted Throttle and Denali Electronics.

We are going places through both organic and acquired growth. With headquarters in Melbourne’s South-East, we have established offices and a strong presence that spans across all states of Australia and New Zealand, as well as South Korea, China, Sweden, and the USA.

With our people at the heart of what we do, we continue to foster a culture of excellence, and entrepreneurship that allows potential to flourish whilst keeping our customer at the forefront.

Take the lead…

Newly created with an opportunity to make the role your own, as our Data and BI Engineer you will be responsible for turning raw data into meaningful insights, delivering the activation required to convert those insights into measurable business outcomes that improve performance and efficiency and using the data to accelerate our business.

Showcasing your technical expertise, broad experience and demonstrated business partnering skills, you will work closely with functional heads, taking the time to understand the business requirements to ensure our data translates into real-world impact across operations, sales, and key business strategies.

It’s you, front and centre, driving activity, identifying opportunities for continuous improvement, and supporting our efforts through improved reporting capabilities, improved data quality, data mining and process automation. 

What will give you the competitive edge?

Your proven ability to deliver not only insights but also actions that drive tangible business outcomes will become your trademark and see you transition into the business with ease. You will be in your element capturing hearts and minds whilst being in the thick of the action to drive our business transformations.  Ideally you will also have:

Formal qualifications in data analytics, statistics, computer science, or related field.

3+ years of experience in data analysis, business intelligence, or a similar role.

Strong proficiency in SQL, Excel, and at least one BI tool (preferably Power BI).

Experience with data modelling and data visualisation.

Excellent communication and presentation skills.

Desirable

Experience working with cloud data platforms (e.g., Azure, Fabric, AWS, Snowflake etc.).

Knowledge of advanced analytics.

Knowledge of leveraging and enhancing data using AI and ML tools.

Familiarity with data governance, data quality frameworks, and data compliance standards.

Experience in a global or multi-site organisation.

What’s in it for you?

Work with industry leader, part of ASX listed Amotiv Limited, one of Australia’s leading conglomerates of automotive aftermarket product brands

Help us transform our company from grass roots up

Open and collaborative culture and management style

Employee recognition programs and initiatives

A people first culture with a focus on wellness, with comprehensive, safety and well-being support

Competitive salary and employee benefits/staff discounts and Paid Parental leave

Structured leadership and development programs providing an environment that allows potential to flourish

About Us
Canberra Consulting focuses on delivering highly skilled and qualified professionals to our clients. We have the experience and capability to understand your specific requirements and match them to the right environment, ensuring professional satisfaction and development. We focus on fit — for both our clients and our candidates — and give you every opportunity to thrive.

The Opportunity
Join a specialist team supporting Defence on a multi-year program. You’ll be the technical lead for data observability and analytics across lab and field activities, enabling system-of-systems test & evaluation, risk reduction and experimentation. Some interstate and occasional international travel may be required for trials and stakeholder engagements.

Key Responsibilities

Design, build and implement data observability & analytics tooling for LCS Validation Labs and initiatives.
Establish and maintain observability practices for T&E and experimentation; perform root-cause analysis and optimisation.
Provide SME advice, collaborate with validation and engineering teams, and influence future architectures.
Integrate observability into DevSecOps/automation (e.g., CI/CD, build/test pipelines).
Support exercises, trials and field activities; deliver reports and post-activity assessments.
Mentor and train ADF personnel; contribute to innovation and integration of deployable systems.
Skills & Experience
Required

Extensive Data Observation/Analytics experience.
Advanced Linux (RHEL) administration.
DevSecOps (CI/CD, GitLab) and automation background.
Coding/scripting: Python, Bash, PowerShell (plus Java/C/C++ advantageous).
API development/integration proficiency.
Solid networking, storage, virtualisation (KVM, VMware).
Defence/government experience with NV1/NV2; familiarity with secure environments and emerging tech.
Desirable

Industry certs in Data Engineering (AWS/Azure/GCP), observability (Datadog/New Relic/Prometheus/Grafana).
Tertiary quals in data/IT/engineering; 10+ years in data engineering/analytics; systems engineering exposure.
Defence test & evaluation experience; familiarity with Agile delivery.
Security Clearance
You must be an Australian Citizen and hold a minimum NV1 clearance. Candidates may be required to undergo an upgrade to NV2.
Note: Candidates not meeting the Security requirements above will not be considered.

Apply Now
Does this sound like a perfect role for you? Interested in hearing more? Contact our Recruitment Director, Alister, at Alister@canberraconsulting.com.au to arrange a confidential discussion.

Software Engineer (AI Product) Sequoia-backed Scale-up | Sydney (Hybrid)

$140k + super + equity

Want to work on production AI serving thousands of customers globally?

If so, you could join a Sequoia-backed team building an AI-powered workflow platform that’s changing how global companies automate and scale their operations.

Having just received a $20m funding Sequoia, they are now taking their AI tools to production and they’re looking for smart, ambitious engineers to help shape the product.

This is a chance to join the AI team in a scaling start-up early, where your ideas and code make a direct impact, and you’re surrounded by people who genuinely love what they do.

Why join

A company that truly lives its values where everyone describes the team as supportive, ambitious, and genuinely good humans to work with.

Culture of autonomy and trust with high flexibility, low ego and high impact. Engineers are trusted to take ownership and make decisions but you’ll also have the support of a seriously impressive team around you.

You’d work across modern technologies including TypeScript, React, Node.js, Golang, and AWS, learning from experienced product engineers in a collaborative environment. You’ll build real-world AI and ship features that bring AI into everyday workflows for enterprise users. This isn’t an ML role, it;s pure software but you’ll be working with LLMs and integrating AI into the platform.

It’s hybrid work from their Sydney CBD office (Tuesdays & Fridays), fully stocked kitchen, team lunches, regular social events, and epic annual offsites (Bali, Korea and Malaysia were the last three).

The Role

As a Software Engineer for the AI product, you’ll work within a small team, building greenfield products.

You’ll:


Work across the stack using React, TypeScript, Node.js


Build and maintain scalable systems on AWS


Collaborate on AI integrations that deliver real customer value


Be part of a product journey from beta to full-scale production


This is a great opportunity for someone mid-level 2 years’ experience who wants to learn fast, work with cutting-edge tech, and see their work make an impact.

You’ll need to be product focused - if you expect to be given tickets and they go off and work on them, this won’t happen. You’ll be working with the AI lead to understand what impact these solutions have in the real-world and deliver them.

Apply here

Working at Atlassian

Atlassians can choose where they work – whether in an office, from home, or a combination of the two. That way, Atlassians have more control over supporting their family, personal goals, and other priorities. We can hire people in any country where we have a legal entity.

About Central AI Org


Our organization is dedicated to driving AI innovation across all Atlassian products and platforms. We aim to deliver seamless AI experiences while establishing a robust Atlassian AI infrastructure for the future. Our purpose is to:

Develop horizontal AI capabilities and infrastructure that can be leveraged across all products.

Establish a centralized Search, Q&A, and Conversational AI system that integrates seamlessly with all Atlassian products.

Explore the integration of Atlassian products with AI solutions beyond the Atlassian ecosystem.

About AI & ML Platform Team


Our team’s goal is to build the foundations to democratize AI and Machine Learning for Atlassian’s teams, customers, and ecosystem. We aim to build productive and reliable tools that empower Atlassian teams to harness the power of AI. These tools will facilitate the development, deployment, measurement, and operation of AI & ML experiences.

Our tools are designed to integrate seamlessly with other Atlassian platforms, including the Atlassian Data Platform. This integration enables teams to efficiently and swiftly incorporate AI and ML capabilities into their workflows while strictly adhering to all security and data usage policies. Our primary goal is to deliver a smooth and hassle-free experience for Atlassian users, empowering them to harness the potential of AI and ML without any complications.

About This Role


As a Principal ML System Engineer on the AI & ML Platform team, you will play a pivotal role in developing and refining the core infrastructure that empowers all Atlassian software engineers, ML engineers, and data scientists to create, train, evaluate, deploy, and manage Machine Learning models and pipelines.

You will collaborate closely with product teams, such as Jira and Confluence, to solve their specific challenges in building ML solutions. This may involve curating high-quality ML datasets, fine-tuning open-sourced Large Language Models (LLMs), or accessing proprietary LLMs. Your expertise in both ML and software development expertise will be instrumental in overcoming challenging problems and navigating complex infrastructure and architectural issues.

This position offers you the chance to lead projects from the technical design phase all the way to launch. You will partner with various teams and internal stakeholders to achieve impactful results.

In this role, you'll get the chance to:

Collaborate with your teammates to solve complex problems, from technical design to launch.

Deliver cutting-edge solutions that are used by other Atlassian teams and products to build AI features that reach millions of customers.

Deliver code reviews, documentation & bug fixes within a strong engineering culture

Partner across engineering teams to take on company-wide initiatives spanning multiple projects.

Mentor junior members of the team.

On your first day, we’ll expect you to have


5+ years of experience in building Machine Learning and AI infra/platform/system

Comprehensive ML lifecycle expertise: proven experience developing, deploying, and maintaining end-to-end ML systems, from data engineering to model serving and monitoring.

Large-scale system design: Extensive experience designing and building scalable, fault-tolerant, and high-performance distributed systems for machine learning.

Proficiency with frameworks and languages: Expert-level proficiency in Python and ML frameworks like PyTorch, TensorFlow, or JAX. Familiarity with other languages like Go, Java, or Scala is also beneficial.

MLOps and automation: Deep experience implementing MLOps, CI/CD pipelines, and automation for continuous training, deployment, and monitoring of ML models.

It would be great, but not required if you have


Cloud infrastructure: Hands-on expertise with major cloud platforms such as AWS, GCP, or Azure, including their specific AI/ML services and compute resources like GPUs.

Big data processing: Experience with distributed computing frameworks for large-scale data processing, such as Spark, Ray, or Dask.

Performance optimization: A demonstrated ability to diagnose and solve complex performance and optimization problems for ML models and infrastructure.

Generative AI systems: Experience with GenAI frameworks and tools, including developing and fine-tuning large language models (LLMs) and building retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) systems. 

Atlassian offers a wide range of perks and benefits designed to support you, your family and to help you engage with your local community. Our offerings include health and wellbeing resources, paid volunteer days, and so much more. To learn more, visit go.atlassian.com/perksandbenefits.

About Atlassian

At Atlassian, we're motivated by a common goal: to unleash the potential of every team. Our software products help teams all over the planet and our solutions are designed for all types of work. Team collaboration through our tools makes what may be impossible alone, possible together.

We believe that the unique contributions of all Atlassians create our success. To ensure that our products and culture continue to incorporate everyone's perspectives and experience, we never discriminate based on race, religion, national origin, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, age, or marital, veteran, or disability status. All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.

To provide you the best experience, we can support with accommodations or adjustments at any stage of the recruitment process. Simply inform our Recruitment team during your conversation with them.

To learn more about our culture and hiring process, visit go.atlassian.com/crh.
